---
import BaseLayout from '../../layout/BaseLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/reports/mcp-tool-test.css';
---
<BaseLayout
  pageTitle="Can LLMs Use Real-World Tools? — MCP Tool Eval"
  description="We gave 39 models access to a Rivian owner's real driving and charging data via MCP tools and asked them to summarize 10 days of activity. Most can call tools. Far fewer call the right tools."
  category="studio"
  fullWidth
  bodyClass="bg-[#f8f6f1]"
>

<div class="report-scope">
<div class="container">

  <!-- Hero -->
  <div class="hero">
    <div class="hero-label">Umwelten MCP Evaluation &middot; Run 004</div>
    <h1>Can LLMs use <em>real-world tools</em><br>to tell a story?</h1>
    <p class="hero-subtitle">
      We gave 39 models access to a Rivian owner's real driving and charging data via
      MCP tools and asked them to summarize 10 days of activity. Most models can call
      tools. Far fewer call the <em>right</em> tools with the <em>right</em> parameters
      and weave the results into an engaging narrative.
    </p>
    <div class="hero-meta">
      <span>39 models</span>
      <span>8 providers</span>
      <span>$0.96 total</span>
      <span>Feb 27 &ndash; Mar 8, 2026</span>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="stats-row">
    <div class="stat-card s-green"><div class="stat-num">17</div><div class="stat-label">Perfect 15/15</div></div>
    <div class="stat-card s-accent"><div class="stat-num">8.6s</div><div class="stat-label">Fastest Perfect</div></div>
    <div class="stat-card s-yellow"><div class="stat-num">$0.001</div><div class="stat-label">Cheapest Perfect</div></div>
    <div class="stat-card s-red"><div class="stat-num">8</div><div class="stat-label">Failed / Errored</div></div>
  </div>

  <!-- The Test -->
  <section>
    <div class="section-num">01 &mdash; The Test</div>
    <h2>What are we measuring?</h2>
    <p class="body-text">
      This evaluation tests something most benchmarks skip: <strong>can a model use external tools
      to answer a question that requires real data?</strong> Not synthetic function calls. Not mock APIs.
      Real tools, connected to a real Rivian R1S via the TezLab MCP server.
    </p>
    <p class="body-text">
      Each model gets the same prompt and the same 20+ MCP tools (get_drives, get_charges,
      get_battery_health, etc.). It must figure out which to call, pass the right date parameters,
      and synthesize raw JSON into a narrative a human would want to read.
    </p>
    <div class="question-block">
      <div class="q-label">The Prompt</div>
      <blockquote>
        Look through my real data and summarize the 10 days of the Rivian's activity between
        February 27 and March 8, 2026. If there were any notable trips, create a narrative of
        the time frame. Today is Mar 8 2026 and make sure that you include the full 10 days,
        so if you don't have any drives and chargers in February it's obviously false.
      </blockquote>
    </div>
    <p class="body-text">
      The last sentence is a trap. Models that call <code>get_drives</code> without a
      <code>start_date</code> get only recent data (biased toward March), then confidently
      write a summary that misses the first days. The judge catches this.
    </p>
  </section>

  <!-- Scoring -->
  <section>
    <div class="section-num">02 &mdash; Scoring</div>
    <h2>How we score</h2>
    <p class="body-text">
      Two independent axes: did the model <em>call the right tools</em> (deterministic),
      and did it <em>write a good summary</em> (judged by Claude Haiku 4.5). Total: 0&ndash;15.
    </p>
    <div class="scoring-grid">
      <div class="scoring-card">
        <h4>Tool Score (0&ndash;5, deterministic)</h4>
        <ul>
          <li>Called <code>get_drives</code></li>
          <li>Called <code>get_charges</code></li>
          <li><code>get_drives</code> included <code>start_date</code></li>
          <li><code>get_charges</code> included <code>start_date</code></li>
          <li>At least one start_date &le; Feb 27</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="scoring-card">
        <h4>LLM Judge Score (0&ndash;10)</h4>
        <ul>
          <li>Covers full Feb 27 &ndash; Mar 8 range</li>
          <li>Contains a trip narrative (not just bullets)</li>
          <li>Narrative quality (1&ndash;5)</li>
          <li>Factual grounding from real data (1&ndash;5)</li>
          <li>Combined into overall score (1&ndash;10)</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Findings -->
  <section>
    <div class="section-num">03 &mdash; Key Findings</div>
    <h2>What we learned</h2>
    <div class="finding-grid">
      <div class="finding-card"><div class="f-icon">&#9889;</div><h4>Speed doesn't sacrifice quality</h4><p><strong>Mercury-2</strong> delivered a perfect 15/15 in 8.6s at $0.006.</p></div>
      <div class="finding-card"><div class="f-icon">&#128176;</div><h4>Open-source punches above cost</h4><p><strong>GPT-OSS-120B</strong> scored 15/15 for $0.001 &mdash; 14,303 pts/$.</p></div>
      <div class="finding-card"><div class="f-icon">&#127968;</div><h4>Local models hold their own</h4><p><strong>GLM-4.7-flash</strong> on Ollama scored 14/15, zero API cost.</p></div>
      <div class="finding-card"><div class="f-icon">&#128165;</div><h4>The date trap works</h4><p>Models skipping <code>start_date</code> get truncated data and write wrong summaries.</p></div>
      <div class="finding-card"><div class="f-icon">&#128683;</div><h4>Tool calling isn't universal</h4><p>8 models failed outright &mdash; DeepSeek R1, Phi-4, Gemma 3N lack tool support.</p></div>
      <div class="finding-card"><div class="f-icon">&#128171;</div><h4>Qwen 3.5 dominates value</h4><p>All four Qwen 3.5 variants scored 15/15. Flash: $0.003 in 22s.</p></div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Results -->
  <section>
    <div class="section-num">04 &mdash; Results</div>
    <h2>Full rankings</h2>
    <p class="body-text">Click any row to see the full response, tool-calling thread, and judge verdict.</p>
    <div class="table-controls">
      <input type="text" id="search" placeholder="Search models...">
      <button class="filter-btn active" data-f="all">All</button>
      <button class="filter-btn" data-f="perfect">Perfect</button>
      <button class="filter-btn" data-f="cloud">Cloud</button>
      <button class="filter-btn" data-f="local">Local</button>
    </div>
    <div class="range-filters">
      <div class="range-filter">
        <label>Max cost</label>
        <input type="range" id="filter-cost" min="0" max="100" value="100">
        <span class="range-val" id="filter-cost-val">any</span>
      </div>
      <div class="range-filter">
        <label>Max time</label>
        <input type="range" id="filter-time" min="0" max="100" value="100">
        <span class="range-val" id="filter-time-val">any</span>
      </div>
      <div class="range-filter">
        <label>Min score</label>
        <input type="range" id="filter-score" min="0" max="15" value="0">
        <span class="range-val" id="filter-score-val">any</span>
      </div>
      <div class="range-filter">
        <label>Min Elo</label>
        <input type="range" id="filter-elo" min="1200" max="1800" value="1200" step="10">
        <span class="range-val" id="filter-elo-val">any</span>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="filter-summary" id="filter-summary"></div>
    <div class="results-table-wrap">
      <table>
        <thead><tr>
          <th data-sort="rank">#</th>
          <th data-sort="model">Model</th>
          <th data-sort="total">Total</th>
          <th data-sort="llm">LLM</th>
          <th data-sort="tools">Tools</th>
          <th data-sort="time">Time</th>
          <th data-sort="cost">Cost</th>
          <th data-sort="value">pts/$</th>
          <th data-sort="elo">Elo</th>
          <th>Story</th>
          <th>Facts</th>
          <th>Feb?</th>
        </tr></thead>
        <tbody id="results-body"></tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Detail Panel -->
  <div class="detail-panel" id="detail-panel">
    <div class="detail-header">
      <div>
        <h3 id="detail-title"></h3>
        <span id="detail-subtitle" style="font-size:0.85rem;color:var(--ink-faint);"></span>
      </div>
      <div class="nav-arrows">
        <button class="nav-btn" id="prev-btn">&larr; Prev</button>
        <button class="nav-btn" id="next-btn">Next &rarr;</button>
        <button class="detail-close" id="close-btn">Close &times;</button>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="detail-stats" id="detail-stats"></div>
    <div class="detail-tabs">
      <button class="detail-tab active" data-tab="response">Response</button>
      <button class="detail-tab" data-tab="thread">Thread</button>
      <button class="detail-tab" data-tab="judge">Judge</button>
    </div>
    <div class="tab-content active" id="tab-response">
      <div class="rendered-md" id="rendered-response"><p class="loading">Loading...</p></div>
    </div>
    <div class="tab-content" id="tab-thread">
      <div class="thread" id="thread-view"><p class="loading">Loading...</p></div>
    </div>
    <div class="tab-content" id="tab-judge">
      <div id="judge-view"></div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Elo Rankings -->
  <section id="elo-section" style="display:none">
    <div class="section-num">05 &mdash; Narrative Rankings</div>
    <h2>Who tells the best story?</h2>
    <p class="body-text">
      The judge score rates each model in isolation. But how do models compare <em>head-to-head</em>?
      We ran a Swiss-style pairwise tournament: Claude Haiku 4.5 reads two narratives side-by-side
      (randomly ordered to avoid position bias) and picks the better one. Results feed into
      Bradley-Terry/Elo ratings.
    </p>
    <p class="body-text" id="elo-meta" style="font-family:var(--mono);font-size:0.82rem;color:var(--ink-faint)"></p>
    <div class="results-table-wrap">
      <table>
        <thead><tr>
          <th>#</th><th>Model</th><th>Elo</th><th>W</th><th>L</th><th>T</th><th>Tools</th>
        </tr></thead>
        <tbody id="elo-body"></tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Errors -->
  <section>
    <div class="section-num">06 &mdash; Failures</div>
    <h2>Models that couldn't complete the test</h2>
    <p class="body-text">
      These models lack tool-calling support or aren't available. Choosing a model
      that can't use tools wastes time and money.
    </p>
    <div class="results-table-wrap">
      <table>
        <thead><tr><th>Model</th><th>Provider</th><th>Error</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody id="errors-body"></tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Methodology -->
  <section>
    <div class="section-num">07 &mdash; Methodology</div>
    <h2>How the test was run</h2>
    <p class="body-text">
      Sequential model runs against a shared TezLab MCP connection via OAuth.
      Same system prompt, same 20+ read-only tools, up to 20 tool-calling steps.
      Vehicle commands filtered via MCP annotations.
    </p>
    <p class="body-text">
      Responses cached per-run. Judge: Claude Haiku 4.5 via OpenRouter, temperature 0.0.
      Cost metered by OpenRouter; Ollama = "local" / $0.
      Duration = wall-clock including all tool round trips.
    </p>
  </section>

  <div class="report-footer">
    Generated by <a href="https://thefocus.ai">Focus.AI</a> Umwelten &middot;
    Run 004 &middot; Feb 27 &ndash; Mar 8, 2026
  </div>
</div>
</div><!-- end .report-scope -->

<script is:inline src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/marked/marked.min.js"></script>
<script is:inline>
const DATA_BASE = '/reports/mcp-tool-test';
let DATA = [];
let ERRORS = [];
let ELO = {};
let currentFilter = 'all';
let sortCol = 'rank';
let sortAsc = true;
let currentIdx = -1;
let detailCache = {};

// Load index data
Promise.all([
  fetch(DATA_BASE + '/index-data.json').then(r => r.json()),
  fetch(DATA_BASE + '/elo-data.json').then(r => r.json()).catch(() => ({ lookup: {} })),
]).then(([d, elo]) => {
  DATA = d.judged;
  ERRORS = d.errors;
  ELO = elo.lookup || {};
  renderTable();
  renderErrors();
  if (elo.ranked) renderEloSection(elo);
}).catch(e => console.error('Failed to load data:', e));

// Helpers
function esc(s) {
  if (!s) return '';
  const d = document.createElement('div');
  d.textContent = s;
  return d.innerHTML;
}

function costStr(c) { return c > 0 ? '$' + c.toFixed(4) : 'local'; }
function ptsPerDollar(d) { return d.cost > 0 ? (d.total / d.cost).toFixed(1) : '\u2014'; }
function eloStr(d) {
  const e = ELO[d.key];
  if (!e) return '\u2014';
  const v = e.elo;
  const cls = v > 1520 ? 'color:var(--green)' : v < 1480 ? 'color:var(--red)' : 'color:var(--ink-light)';
  return '<span style="font-family:var(--mono);font-size:0.8rem;' + cls + '">' + v + '</span>';
}

function rowClass(t) {
  if (t >= 15) return 'row-15';
  if (t >= 14) return 'row-14';
  if (t >= 8) return 'row-mid';
  return 'row-low';
}

function qualityBar(val, max) {
  let h = '<span class="quality-bar">';
  for (let i = 0; i < max; i++) {
    const cls = i < val ? (val >= 4 ? 'filled' : val >= 2 ? 'filled-mid' : 'filled-low') : '';
    h += '<span class="' + cls + '"></span>';
  }
  return h + '</span>';
}

function modelHtml(d) {
  const m = d.model;
  const i = m.indexOf('/');
  if (i > 0) return '<span style="color:var(--ink-faint)">' + esc(m.slice(0,i+1)) + '</span>' + esc(m.slice(i+1));
  return esc(m);
}

function badgeFor(d) {
  return d.provider === 'ollama' ? ' <span class="badge badge-local">local</span>' : '';
}

// Range filters
let maxCostFilter = Infinity;
let maxTimeFilter = Infinity;
let minScoreFilter = 0;
let minEloFilter = 0;

function updateFilters() {
  const costSlider = document.getElementById('filter-cost');
  const timeSlider = document.getElementById('filter-time');
  const scoreSlider = document.getElementById('filter-score');
  const eloSlider = document.getElementById('filter-elo');

  const costPct = parseInt(costSlider.value);
  if (costPct >= 100) {
    maxCostFilter = Infinity;
    document.getElementById('filter-cost-val').textContent = 'any';
  } else {
    maxCostFilter = costPct === 0 ? 0 : Math.pow(costPct / 100, 2) * 0.3;
    document.getElementById('filter-cost-val').textContent = maxCostFilter === 0 ? 'local' : '$' + maxCostFilter.toFixed(4);
  }

  const timePct = parseInt(timeSlider.value);
  if (timePct >= 100) {
    maxTimeFilter = Infinity;
    document.getElementById('filter-time-val').textContent = 'any';
  } else {
    maxTimeFilter = timePct * 4;
    document.getElementById('filter-time-val').textContent = maxTimeFilter + 's';
  }

  minScoreFilter = parseInt(scoreSlider.value);
  document.getElementById('filter-score-val').textContent = minScoreFilter === 0 ? 'any' : minScoreFilter + '/15';

  minEloFilter = parseInt(eloSlider.value);
  document.getElementById('filter-elo-val').textContent = minEloFilter <= 1200 ? 'any' : minEloFilter;

  renderTable();
}

// Table
function getVisible() {
  let list = [...DATA];
  const q = document.getElementById('search').value.toLowerCase();
  if (q) list = list.filter(d => d.model.toLowerCase().includes(q) || d.provider.includes(q));
  if (currentFilter === 'perfect') list = list.filter(d => d.total >= 15);
  if (currentFilter === 'cloud') list = list.filter(d => d.provider !== 'ollama');
  if (currentFilter === 'local') list = list.filter(d => d.provider === 'ollama');

  if (maxCostFilter !== Infinity) {
    list = list.filter(d => maxCostFilter === 0 ? (d.cost === 0 || !d.cost) : d.cost <= maxCostFilter || d.cost === 0);
  }
  if (maxTimeFilter !== Infinity) list = list.filter(d => d.time <= maxTimeFilter);
  if (minScoreFilter > 0) list = list.filter(d => d.total >= minScoreFilter);
  if (minEloFilter > 1200) list = list.filter(d => (ELO[d.key]?.elo || 1500) >= minEloFilter);

  list.sort((a, b) => {
    let av, bv;
    switch (sortCol) {
      case 'model': av = a.model; bv = b.model; return sortAsc ? av.localeCompare(bv) : bv.localeCompare(av);
      case 'total': av = a.total; bv = b.total; break;
      case 'llm': av = a.llm; bv = b.llm; break;
      case 'tools': av = a.tools; bv = b.tools; break;
      case 'time': av = a.time; bv = b.time; return sortAsc ? av-bv : bv-av;
      case 'cost': av = a.cost||9999; bv = b.cost||9999; return sortAsc ? av-bv : bv-av;
      case 'value': av = a.cost>0?a.total/a.cost:-1; bv = b.cost>0?b.total/b.cost:-1; break;
      case 'elo': av = ELO[a.key]?.elo||1500; bv = ELO[b.key]?.elo||1500; break;
      default: av = a.total; bv = b.total;
    }
    let d = sortAsc ? av-bv : bv-av;
    if (d === 0) d = a.time - b.time;
    return d;
  });
  return list;
}

function renderTable() {
  const list = getVisible();
  const total = DATA.length;
  const shown = list.length;
  const summaryEl = document.getElementById('filter-summary');
  if (summaryEl) {
    summaryEl.textContent = shown < total ? shown + ' of ' + total + ' models shown' : '';
  }
  const tbody = document.getElementById('results-body');
  tbody.innerHTML = list.map((d, i) => {
    const rank = i + 1;
    const medal = rank <= 3 ? ['\ud83e\udd47','\ud83e\udd48','\ud83e\udd49'][rank-1] : rank;
    const sel = currentIdx >= 0 && DATA[currentIdx].key === d.key ? ' selected' : '';
    return '<tr class="' + rowClass(d.total) + sel + '" data-key="' + d.key + '" style="cursor:pointer">' +
      '<td style="font-weight:700">' + medal + '</td>' +
      '<td style="font-family:var(--mono);font-size:0.82rem">' + modelHtml(d) + badgeFor(d) + '</td>' +
      '<td><strong>' + d.total + '</strong>/15</td>' +
      '<td>' + d.llm + '/10</td>' +
      '<td>' + d.tools + '/5</td>' +
      '<td class="time-cell">' + d.time + 's</td>' +
      '<td class="cost-cell">' + costStr(d.cost) + '</td>' +
      '<td class="cost-cell">' + ptsPerDollar(d) + '</td>' +
      '<td class="elo-cell">' + eloStr(d) + '</td>' +
      '<td>' + qualityBar(d.story, 5) + '</td>' +
      '<td>' + qualityBar(d.facts, 5) + '</td>' +
      '<td>' + (d.feb ? '\u2705' : '\u274c') + '</td>' +
    '</tr>';
  }).join('');
}

function renderErrors() {
  document.getElementById('errors-body').innerHTML = ERRORS.map(e => {
    const m = e.model; const i = m.indexOf('/');
    const mn = i > 0 ? '<span style="color:var(--ink-faint)">' + esc(m.slice(0,i+1)) + '</span>' + esc(m.slice(i+1)) : esc(m);
    return '<tr><td style="font-family:var(--mono);font-size:0.82rem">' + mn + '</td>' +
      '<td><span class="badge badge-' + (e.provider==='ollama'?'local':'error') + '">' + esc(e.provider) + '</span></td>' +
      '<td style="color:var(--ink-faint)">' + esc(e.error) + '</td></tr>';
  }).join('');
}

function setFilter(f) {
  currentFilter = f;
  document.querySelectorAll('.filter-btn').forEach(b => b.classList.toggle('active', b.dataset.f === f));
  renderTable();
}

function sortBy(col) {
  if (sortCol === col) sortAsc = !sortAsc;
  else { sortCol = col; sortAsc = col==='model'||col==='time'||col==='cost'; }
  renderTable();
}

// Detail
async function loadDetail(key) {
  if (detailCache[key]) return detailCache[key];
  try {
    const r = await fetch(DATA_BASE + '/details/' + key + '.json');
    const d = await r.json();
    detailCache[key] = d;
    return d;
  } catch (e) {
    return { responseText: '', transcript: [] };
  }
}

async function showDetail(key) {
  currentIdx = DATA.findIndex(d => d.key === key);
  if (currentIdx < 0) return;
  const d = DATA[currentIdx];

  document.getElementById('detail-title').textContent =
    (d.provider === 'ollama' ? 'ollama:' : 'openrouter:') + d.model;
  document.getElementById('detail-subtitle').textContent = d.explanation;

  document.getElementById('detail-stats').innerHTML = [
    {k:'Total', v:d.total+'/15'}, {k:'LLM Judge', v:d.llm+'/10'}, {k:'Tool Score', v:d.tools+'/5'},
    {k:'Time', v:d.time+'s'}, {k:'Cost', v:costStr(d.cost)}, {k:'pts/$', v:ptsPerDollar(d)},
    {k:'Elo', v: ELO[d.key] ? String(ELO[d.key].elo) : '\u2014'},
    {k:'Narrative', v:d.story+'/5'}, {k:'Factual', v:d.facts+'/5'},
  ].map(s => '<div class="detail-stat"><div class="k">'+s.k+'</div><div class="v">'+s.v+'</div></div>').join('');

  document.getElementById('rendered-response').innerHTML = '<p class="loading">Loading response...</p>';
  document.getElementById('thread-view').innerHTML = '<p class="loading">Loading thread...</p>';
  renderJudge(d);

  document.getElementById('prev-btn').disabled = currentIdx <= 0;
  document.getElementById('next-btn').disabled = currentIdx >= DATA.length - 1;

  document.getElementById('detail-panel').classList.add('open');
  switchTab('response');
  renderTable();
  document.getElementById('detail-panel').scrollIntoView({ behavior: 'smooth', block: 'nearest' });

  const detail = await loadDetail(key);
  if (DATA[currentIdx].key !== key) return;

  if (detail.responseText) {
    document.getElementById('rendered-response').innerHTML = marked.parse(detail.responseText);
  } else {
    document.getElementById('rendered-response').innerHTML = '<p class="loading">No response text available.</p>';
  }

  renderThread(detail.transcript);
}

function renderThread(transcript) {
  const el = document.getElementById('thread-view');
  if (!transcript || transcript.length === 0) {
    el.innerHTML = '<p class="loading">No transcript data available.</p>';
    return;
  }
  let html = '';
  let step = 0;
  for (const msg of transcript) {
    if (msg.role === 'user' && msg.type === 'text') {
      html += '<div class="thread-msg user"><div class="msg-role">User</div><div>' +
        esc(msg.text).replace(/\n/g, '<br>') + '</div></div>';
    } else if (msg.role === 'assistant' && msg.type === 'text') {
      html += '<div class="thread-msg assistant-text"><div class="msg-role">Assistant &mdash; Final Response</div>' +
        '<div class="rendered-md">' + marked.parse(msg.text) + '</div></div>';
    } else if (msg.type === 'tool-call') {
      step++;
      const args = msg.args ? JSON.stringify(msg.args, null, 2) : '';
      html += '<div class="thread-msg tool-call"><div class="msg-role">Step ' + step + ' &mdash; Tool Call</div>' +
        '<div class="tool-name">' + esc(msg.toolName) + '</div>' +
        (args ? '<pre class="tool-args">' + esc(args) + '</pre>' : '') + '</div>';
    } else if (msg.type === 'tool-result') {
      const full = typeof msg.result === 'string' ? msg.result : JSON.stringify(msg.result, null, 2);
      const short = full.length > 400;
      const id = 'tr' + Math.random().toString(36).slice(2,8);
      html += '<div class="thread-msg tool-result"><div class="msg-role">Tool Result</div>' +
        '<div class="tool-result-body" id="' + id + '">' + esc(short ? full.slice(0, 400) + '...' : full) + '</div>';
      if (short) {
        html += '<button class="tool-result-toggle" data-target="' + id + '">Show full result</button>';
      }
      html += '</div>';
      if (short) {
        setTimeout(() => {
          const node = document.getElementById(id);
          if (node) node.dataset.full = full;
        }, 0);
      }
    }
  }
  el.innerHTML = html;
}

function toggleResult(btn, id) {
  const el = document.getElementById(id);
  if (!el) return;
  if (btn.textContent.startsWith('Show')) {
    el.textContent = el.dataset.full || el.textContent;
    btn.textContent = 'Collapse';
    el.style.maxHeight = '600px';
  } else {
    el.textContent = (el.dataset.full || '').slice(0, 400) + '...';
    btn.textContent = 'Show full result';
    el.style.maxHeight = '150px';
  }
}

function renderJudge(d) {
  const el = document.getElementById('judge-view');
  let html = '<h3 style="margin-bottom:1rem">Judge Verdict</h3>';
  html += [
    ['Covers full date range (Feb 27 \u2013 Mar 8)', d.feb],
    ['Has trip narrative', d.narrative],
  ].map(([label, ok]) =>
    '<div style="padding:0.5rem 0;border-bottom:1px solid var(--bg-alt);font-size:0.9rem">' +
    (ok ? '\u2705' : '\u274c') + ' ' + label + '</div>'
  ).join('');

  html += '<div style="display:grid;grid-template-columns:1fr 1fr;gap:1rem;margin:1.5rem 0">';
  html += '<div style="background:var(--bg-alt);padding:1rem;border-radius:4px"><div style="font-family:var(--mono);font-size:0.7rem;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--ink-faint)">Narrative Quality</div><div style="font-family:var(--serif);font-size:2rem;margin-top:0.2rem">' + d.story + '<span style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--ink-faint)">/5</span></div></div>';
  html += '<div style="background:var(--bg-alt);padding:1rem;border-radius:4px"><div style="font-family:var(--mono);font-size:0.7rem;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--ink-faint)">Factual Grounding</div><div style="font-family:var(--serif);font-size:2rem;margin-top:0.2rem">' + d.facts + '<span style="font-size:1rem;color:var(--ink-faint)">/5</span></div></div>';
  html += '</div>';
  html += '<div style="background:var(--bg-alt);padding:1rem;border-radius:4px;margin-bottom:1rem"><div style="font-family:var(--mono);font-size:0.7rem;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--ink-faint)">Overall Score</div><div style="font-family:var(--serif);font-size:2.5rem;margin-top:0.2rem">' + d.llm + '<span style="font-size:1.2rem;color:var(--ink-faint)">/10</span></div></div>';
  html += '<p style="color:var(--ink-light);font-size:0.9rem;max-width:600px"><strong>Explanation:</strong> ' + esc(d.explanation) + '</p>';
  el.innerHTML = html;
}

function switchTab(name) {
  document.querySelectorAll('.detail-tab').forEach(t => t.classList.toggle('active', t.dataset.tab === name));
  document.querySelectorAll('.tab-content').forEach(t => t.classList.remove('active'));
  document.getElementById('tab-' + name).classList.add('active');
}

function navModel(dir) {
  const next = currentIdx + dir;
  if (next >= 0 && next < DATA.length) showDetail(DATA[next].key);
}

function closeDetail() {
  document.getElementById('detail-panel').classList.remove('open');
  currentIdx = -1;
  renderTable();
}

function renderEloSection(elo) {
  document.getElementById('elo-section').style.display = '';
  document.getElementById('elo-meta').textContent =
    elo.mode + ' \u2022 ' + elo.comparisons + ' comparisons \u2022 judge: ' + elo.judge;

  document.getElementById('elo-body').innerHTML = elo.ranked.map((r, i) => {
    const rank = i + 1;
    const medal = rank <= 3 ? ['\ud83e\udd47','\ud83e\udd48','\ud83e\udd49'][rank-1] : rank;
    const label = r.provider + ':' + r.model;
    const cls = r.elo > 1520 ? 'color:var(--green)' : r.elo < 1480 ? 'color:var(--red)' : '';
    return '<tr data-elo-key="' + r.key + '" style="cursor:pointer">' +
      '<td style="font-weight:700">' + medal + '</td>' +
      '<td style="font-family:var(--mono);font-size:0.82rem">' + esc(label) + '</td>' +
      '<td style="font-family:var(--mono);font-weight:700;' + cls + '">' + r.elo + '</td>' +
      '<td>' + r.wins + '</td><td>' + r.losses + '</td><td>' + r.ties + '</td>' +
      '<td>' + r.toolScore + '/5</td></tr>';
  }).join('');
}

// Event delegation (no inline onclick handlers)
document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', () => {
  // Filter buttons
  document.querySelectorAll('.filter-btn').forEach(btn => {
    btn.addEventListener('click', () => setFilter(btn.dataset.f));
  });

  // Range filters
  ['filter-cost', 'filter-time', 'filter-score', 'filter-elo'].forEach(id => {
    document.getElementById(id)?.addEventListener('input', updateFilters);
  });

  // Search input
  document.getElementById('search')?.addEventListener('input', renderTable);

  // Sort headers
  document.querySelectorAll('th[data-sort]').forEach(th => {
    th.addEventListener('click', () => sortBy(th.dataset.sort));
  });

  // Table row clicks
  document.getElementById('results-body')?.addEventListener('click', (e) => {
    const tr = e.target.closest('tr[data-key]');
    if (tr) showDetail(tr.dataset.key);
  });

  // Elo row clicks
  document.getElementById('elo-body')?.addEventListener('click', (e) => {
    const tr = e.target.closest('tr[data-elo-key]');
    if (tr) showDetail(tr.dataset.eloKey);
  });

  // Detail panel buttons
  document.getElementById('prev-btn')?.addEventListener('click', () => navModel(-1));
  document.getElementById('next-btn')?.addEventListener('click', () => navModel(1));
  document.getElementById('close-btn')?.addEventListener('click', closeDetail);

  // Tab buttons
  document.querySelectorAll('.detail-tab').forEach(tab => {
    tab.addEventListener('click', () => switchTab(tab.dataset.tab));
  });

  // Tool result toggles (delegated)
  document.addEventListener('click', (e) => {
    if (e.target.classList.contains('tool-result-toggle')) {
      toggleResult(e.target, e.target.dataset.target);
    }
  });

  // Keyboard nav
  document.addEventListener('keydown', e => {
    if (currentIdx >= 0) {
      if (e.key === 'ArrowLeft') { e.preventDefault(); navModel(-1); }
      if (e.key === 'ArrowRight') { e.preventDefault(); navModel(1); }
      if (e.key === 'Escape') closeDetail();
    }
  });
});
</script>

</BaseLayout>
